      "message": "I don\u0027t think this is technically a requirement, though it works for Chrome OS.  Someone (I think Stephen Boyd) pointed to the proper place.  I didn\u0027t do it for trogdor (sorry) but I did mention it in CL:2229355.  I think we want to use:\n\n  /sys/bus/soc/devices/soc0/\n\nDoes that exist for you and work?  For trogdor I get:\n\n  family:Snapdragon\n  revision:1.1\n  soc_id:425\n\nFor cheza I get:\n\n  family:Snapdragon\n  machine:SDM845\n  revision:2.1\n  soc_id:321\n\nHuh, I wonder why it doesn\u0027t have the machine for trogdor?  In any case, maybe this is the right place to be looking?",
